 adversaries.     Share         Service Personnel: Recruitment and Retention      The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Andrew Jones (Harrogate and Knaresborough) (Con)       Share       3. What steps his Department is taking to (a) recruit and (b) retain service personnel.   [900002]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Robert Halfon (Harlow) (Con)       Share       4. What steps his Department is taking to (a) recruit and (b) retain service personnel.   [900003]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Vicky Ford (Chelmsford) (Con)       Share       5. What steps his Department is taking to (a) recruit and (b) retain service personnel.   [900004]     Share                    The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Sir Robert Syms (Poole) (Con)       Share       21. What steps his Department is taking to (a) recruit and (b) retain service personnel.   [900021]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Giles Watling (Clacton) (Con)       Share       24. What steps his Department is taking to (a) recruit and (b) retain service personnel.   [900024]     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     The Minister for the Armed Forces (Mark Lancaster)       Share       We remain committed to maintaining the overall size of the armed forces, and we have a range of measures under way to improve recru